[{"id":"VR803447","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three views of two spheres, labeled 1 and 2, at three different times. In the first view, sphere 1 and sphere 2 are moving toward each other, with sphere 1 moving to the right with charge 10 nanocoulombs and electric potential 900 volts, and with sphere 2 moving to the left with charge 8 nanocoulombs and electric potential 1800 volts. In the second view, the two spheres are in contact with each other, and begin to move apart. In the third view, the two spheres have returned to their original positions, and their charges and electric potentials are now unknown.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803447.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two positively charged metal spheres with different radii are initially separated by a great distance. Initially Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 nanocoulombs\"><math alttext=\"10 nanocoulombs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mtext>10</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>nC</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span> and the electric potential at the surface of Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"900 volts\"><math alttext=\"900 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>900</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>V</mtext></mstyle></math></span></span>. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has charge 